archive-date=2018-12-26 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref>。

== 詞曲 ==
[[File:Drake_fox_theatre.jpg|left]]
《Drake Would Love Me》是一首[[当代节奏布鲁斯|节奏布鲁斯]]歌曲，長達4分19秒<ref name="Sources132" /><ref name="Source1">{{Cite web |url=http://time.com/3613958/k-michelle-drake-would-love-me-anybody-wanna-buy-a-heart/ |title=K. Michelle Wrote a Song About Wanting Drake to Love Her |last=Feeney |first=Nolan |date=2014-12-02 |website=[[時代雜誌|Time]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522030809/http://time.com/3613958/k-michelle-drake-would-love-me-anybody-wanna-buy-a-heart/ |archive-date=2018-05-22 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref>，並以[[謠曲|謠曲]]和{{tsl|en|slow jam|slow jam}}的風格演唱<ref name="Source3" /><ref name="Source7">{{Cite web |url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/kimberly-the-people-i-used-to-know/ |title=Kimberly: The People I Used to Know |last=Soto |first=Alfred |date=2017-12-08 |website=[[Pitchfork_Media|Pitchfork]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180408035111/https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/kimberly-the-people-i-used-to-know/ |archive-date=2018-04-08 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref>。歌曲主要樂器為[[鋼琴|鋼琴]]，而一開始的[[旋律|旋律]]讓{{tsl|en|MTV News|MTV新聞}}的羅伯·馬克曼（{{lang|en|Rob Markman}}）覺得舒緩。當它逐漸推進時，{{tsl|en|guitar lick|吉他樂句}}和[[小提琴|小提琴]]慢慢融入演奏的樂器中<ref name="Source4" />。

歌詞圍繞與德瑞克的幻想戀情，當中提到的情況包括蜜雪兒與德瑞克出席[[葛萊美獎|葛萊美獎]]以及被他[[迷妹|迷妹]]憎恨<ref name="Source3" />。樂評人根據這些歌詞內容將《Drake Would Love Me》跟[[同人小說|同人小說]]聯繫在一起<ref name="Source2">{{Cite web |url=https://jezebel.com/k-michelles-drake-would-love-me-is-basically-fan-ficti-1665726327 |title=K. Michelle's 'Drake Would Love Me' Is Basically Fan Fiction |last=Brown |first=Kara |date=2014-12-02 |website=Jezebel |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160907192815/http://jezebel.com/k-michelles-drake-would-love-me-is-basically-fan-ficti-1665726327 |archive-date=2016-09-07 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref><ref name="Source13">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thefader.com/2014/12/19/listmania-2014 |title=The Fader Presents: Listmania! 2014 |date=2014-12-19 |website=The Fader |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522030809/http://www.thefader.com/2014/12/19/listmania-2014 |archive-date=2018-05-22 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref><ref name="Sources1">{{Cite web |url=http://thequietus.com/articles/16938-r-b-albums-and-singles-of-2014-with-alex-macpherson |title=R&B Albums And Singles of 2014 With Alex Macpherson |last=Macpherson |first=Alex |date=2014-12-18 |website=The Quietus |access-date=2018-05-21}}</ref>。《[[時代雜誌|時代]]》的諾蘭·費尼（{{lang|en|Nolan Feeney}}）打趣地說跟[[亞曼達·拜恩斯|亞曼達·拜恩斯]]在[[Twitter|Twitter]]寫道希望德瑞克「糟蹋（她的）陰道」比較，蜜雪兒過於收斂<ref name="Source1" /><ref name="AmandaBynes1">{{Cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/07/drake-amanda-bynes-tweets_n_3721318.html |title=Drake Comments on Amanda Bynes’ Bizarre Tweets, Calls Them 'Weird And Disturbing' |last=Sieczkowski |first=Cavan |date=2013-08-07 |website=[[哈芬登郵報|HuffPost]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170721171301/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/07/drake-amanda-bynes-tweets_n_3721318.html |archive-date=2017-07-21 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref>。歌詞中「Drake wouldn't leave me, he would keep me, never break his promises / I'd be the best he ever had, he'd be on his best behavior / He would make me so proud / Drake would love me」（大意：德瑞克不會離開我，他會照顧我，從不違背諾言/我會是他最好的女友，而他會舉止得體/他會讓我感到驕傲/德瑞克會愛我），蜜雪兒是參考了德瑞克單曲《{{tsl|en|Best I Ever Had (Drake song)|Best I Ever Had (德瑞克歌曲)|Best I Ever Had}}》、《{{tsl|en|Worst Behavior|Worst Behavior}}》和《{{tsl|en|Make Me Proud|Make Me Proud}}》的曲名<ref name="Source1" /><ref name="MusicTimes1">{{Cite web |url=https://www.musictimes.com/articles/19599/20141210/k-michelle-discusses-drake-love-song-disses-lil-kim-breakfast-club.htm |title=K. Michelle Discusses Her 'Drake Would Love Me' Song And Disses Lil' Kim on The Breakfast Club [Watch] |date=2014-12-10 |website=Music Times |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170427220200/http://www.musictimes.com/articles/19599/20141210/k-michelle-discusses-drake-love-song-disses-lil-kim-breakfast-club.htm |archive-date=2017-04-27 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref>。《音樂時報》（{{lang|en|Music Times}}）的撰稿人認為歌詞體現了德瑞克的音樂中經常圍繞情感的主題<ref name="MusicTimes1" />。蜜雪兒列出德瑞克的正面特質，當中唱道他「始終如一」、「不玩弄感情」和不會撒謊或讓她哭。費尼將這些歌詞的{{tsl|en|rhyme scheme|押韻格式}}與[[蘇斯博士|蘇斯博士]]的寫作風格作比較<ref name="Source1" />。

專輯的最後三首歌（《Build a Man》、《Drake Would Love Me》和《God I Get It》）被樂評人詮釋成是形成一齣有關蜜雪兒愛情觀念的故事<ref name="Sources1" /><ref name="Sources12">{{Cite web |url=http://renownedforsound.com/index.php/album-review-k-michelle-anybody-wanna-buy-a-heart/ |title=Album Review |last=Morris |first=Meggie |date=2014-12-25 |website=Renowned for Sound |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150811172335/http://renownedforsound.com/index.php/album-review-k-michelle-anybody-wanna-buy-a-heart/ |archive-date=2015-08-11 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|The Quietus|The Quietus}}》的亞歷克斯·麥克弗森（{{lang|en|Alex Macpherson}}）稱這些歌曲是蜜雪兒嘗試「讓她同樣需要深愛著現實中遇到的男人」，並認為她在《Build a Man》和《Drake Would Love Me》是開始在《[[科學怪人|科學怪人]]》和同人小說中尋求愛的答案，之後在《God I Get It》接受自身的缺陷<ref name="Sources1" />。《{{tsl|en|Renowned for Sound|聲名遠播}}》的梅吉·莫里斯（{{lang|en|Meggie Morris}}）認為《Drake Would Love Me》是延續了《Build a Man》，因為兩者都圍繞她對完美男性的看法<ref name="Sources12" />。《[[波士頓環球報|波士頓環球報]]》的肯·卡波比亞科（{{lang|en|Ken Capobianco}}）寫道《Drake Would Love Me》呈現了專輯的「誠實、對抗和耽于声色」<ref name="Sources6">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2014/12/23/michelle-anybody-wanna-buy-heart/77lqidGa2ZU2vSXnSDYNaO/story.html |title=K. Michelle, ‘Anybody Wanna Buy a Heart?’ |last=Capobianco |first=Ken |date=2014-12-23 |website=[[波士頓環球報|The Boston Globe]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141227083034/http://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/music/2014/12/23/michelle-anybody-wanna-buy-heart/77lqidGa2ZU2vSXnSDYNaO/story.html |archive-date=2014-12-27 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref>，但《{{tsl|en|Metro New York|紐約大都市}}》的艾米麗·勞倫斯（{{lang|en|Emily Laurence}}）以它舉例說明「不是所有歌曲都充滿強烈情感」<ref name="Source112" />。

== 專業評價 ==
雖然《Drake Would Love Me》與部分樂評人一開始期盼的有所不同，但他們還是十分喜歡<ref name="Sources10">{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2014/12/08/playlist-martin-caballero-j-cole-mark-ronson-snoop-dogg-pusha-t/20106277/ |title=Playlist: What's Martín Caballero listening to? |last=Caballero |first=Martin |date=2014-12-08 |website=[[今日美國|USA Today]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010221438/http://www.usatoday.com/story/life/music/2014/12/08/playlist-martin-caballero-j-cole-mark-ronson-snoop-dogg-pusha-t/20106277/ |archive-date=2016-10-10 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref><ref name="Sources2">{{Cite web |url=http://www.startribune.com/new-music-k-michelle-catfish-and-the-bottlemen/287247631/ |title=New music: K. Michelle, Catfish and the Bottlemen |last=Amorosi |first=A. D. |date=2014-12-31 |website=Star Tribune |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180114034317/http://www.startribune.com/new-music-k-michelle-catfish-and-the-bottlemen/287247631/ |archive-date=2018-01-14 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref>。《[[今日美國|今日美國]]》的馬丁·卡瓦列羅（{{lang|en|Martín Caballero}}）寫道「不要問我們（這首歌）為什麼或如何行得通」，並稱讚它是首「（能登）大雅之堂的節奏藍調謠曲聖歌」<ref name="Sources10" />。雖然《[[費城詢問報|費城詢問報]]》的A·D·艾莫洛溪（{{lang|en|A.D. Amorosi}}）期待一些「滑稽或狂妄（的東西）」，但還是著重指出歌曲並沒有將重點放在暗戀上<ref name="Sources2" />。其他影評人相信歌曲展示了蜜雪兒的幽默感<ref name="Sources12" /><ref name="Newspaper1">{{Cite news |last=Fekadu |first=Mesfin |url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/468460188/ |title=In Case You Missed It |date=2015-01-13 |work=Ottawa Citizen |access-date=2019-09-07 |via=Newspapers.com |archive-date=2020-08-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824105151/https://www.newspapers.com/image/468460188/ |dead-url=no }}{{subscription required}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|Ottawa Citizen|渥太華公民報}}》的梅斯芬·費卡杜（{{lang|en|Mesfin Fekadu}}）說她「聰明又好笑」<ref name="Newspaper1" />，而梅吉·莫里斯稱她的演唱「迷人地風趣」<ref name="Sources12" />。肯·卡波比亞科稱讚蜜雪兒表達情感的水準是「現今節奏藍調歌曲少有的脆弱和具有強烈摩擦的張力」，並認為這是她受歡迎的原因<ref name="Sources6" />。《[[Pitchfork_Media|Pitchfork]]》的阿爾弗雷德·索托（{{lang|en|Alfred Soto}}）讚賞《Drake Would Love Me》有種緊迫感，並相信她用最好的歌聲來演唱它<ref name="Source7" />。

《[[華盛頓郵報|華盛頓郵報]]》的克里斯·理查茲（{{lang|en|Chris Richards}}）認為蜜雪兒發行明顯有關對另名歌手表達愛意的歌曲「有點不太酷」<ref name="Sources9">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2014/12/23/months-best-music-dangelo-charli-xcx-shy-glizzy-and-more/ |title=Month's best music: D’Angelo, Charli XCX, Shy Glizzy and more |last=Richards |first=Chris |date=2014-12-23 |website=[[華盛頓郵報|The Washington Post]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522030809/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/arts-and-entertainment/wp/2014/12/23/months-best-music-dangelo-charli-xcx-shy-glizzy-and-more/?utm_term=.ff154ce8dd9b |archive-date=2018-05-22 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|Jezebel (website)|蕩婦 (網站)|蕩婦}}》的卡拉·布朗（{{lang|en|Kara Brown}}）公開表示這首歌十分不舒服，嚴厲批評它的「音樂性質等同於嘗試阻止你朋友喝醉時發給她一個月前差點勾搭上的男性第三則信息」。布朗說歌詞中德瑞克的形象更像是理想男友，而不是他對女性的實質舉止<ref name="Source2" />。德瑞克曾被一些媒體機構批評他的音樂曾[[厭女症|貶抑女性]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.much.com/she-said-she-said-drakes-lyrics-misogynistic/ |title=She Said, She Said: Are Drake’s Lyrics Misogynistic? |last=Crawford |first=Andi |last2=James |first2=Brianne |date=2016-07-20 |website=Much |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130030222/https://www.much.com/she-said-she-said-drakes-lyrics-misogynistic/ |archive-date=2019-11-30 |accessdate=2020-08-23 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oxygen.com/very-real/6-drake-lyrics-that-are-actually-super-sexist|title=6 Drake Lyrics That Are Actually Super Sexist|last=George|first=Kat|date=2015-10-28|work=Oxygen|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190415174158/https://www.oxygen.com/very-real/6-drake-lyrics-that-are-actually-super-sexist|archive-date=2019-04-15|accessdate=2020-08-24}}</ref><ref name="#1">{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/07/no-guidance-drake-chris-brown-troubling-collaboration/595027/|title=Drake’s Troubling Reunion With Chris Brown|last=Giorgis|first=Hannah|date=2019-07-30|work=[[大西洋_(雜誌)|The Atlantic]]|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130030223/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2019/07/no-guidance-drake-chris-brown-troubling-collaboration/595027/|archive-date=2019-11-30|accessdate=2020-08-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/drake-scorpion-appropriation-mariah-carey-lauryn-hill-nicki-minaj-samples|title=Drake Uses Women's Work On ''Scorpion'' Instead Of Giving Them Their Own Voice|last=Kaplan|first=Ilana|date=2018-07-01|work=Refinery29|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007094440/https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/drake-scorpion-appropriation-mariah-carey-lauryn-hill-nicki-minaj-samples|archive-date=2019-10-07|accessdate=2020-08-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sunday-times/lifestyle/2018-07-07-drake-markets-himself-as-raps-mr-nice-guy-dont-be-fooled/|title=Drake markets himself as rap's Mr Nice Guy. Don't be fooled|last=Tsotetsi|first=Pearl Boshomane|date=2018-07-08|work=The Times|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823055210/https://www.timeslive.co.za/sunday-times/lifestyle/2018-07-07-drake-markets-himself-as-raps-mr-nice-guy-dont-be-fooled/|archive-date=2019-08-23|accessdate=2020-08-24}}</ref>和他與未成年女性之間的關係<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bet.com/style/living/2018/09/24/drake-s-texting-relationship-with-millie-bobby-brown.html |title=Are Drake's Texting Relationship With Underage Female Stars Inappropriate? |date=2018-12-20 |website=[[黑人娛樂電視台|BET]] |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181222160804/https://www.bet.com/style/living/2018/09/24/drake-s-texting-relationship-with-millie-bobby-brown.html |archive-date=2018-12-22 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/14-year-old-millie-bobby-brown-drake-31-text-boys-internet-horrified-called-grooming-162337845.html|title=14-year-old Millie Bobby Brown and Drake, 31, text 'about boys' and the internet is horrified: 'This is called grooming'|last=Byrne|first=Suzy|date=2018-09-19|work=[[雅虎|Yahoo!]]|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191101203654/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/14-year-old-millie-bobby-brown-drake-31-text-boys-internet-horrified-called-grooming-162337845.html|archive-date=2019-11-01|accessdate=2020-08-24}}</ref><ref name="#1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://nylon.com/articles/teen-fan-grooming-drake-borns|title=On Drake, Grooming, And Powerful Men’s Interest In Impressionable Young Women|last=Song|first=Sandra|date=2018-10-02|work=[[Nylon|Nylon]]|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191219153139/https://nylon.com/articles/teen-fan-grooming-drake-borns|archive-date=2019-12-19|accessdate=2020-08-24}}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|Complex (magazine)|Complex (雜誌)|Complex}}》的{{tsl|en|Michael Arceneaux|邁克爾·阿爾森諾}}表示聽者會意識到歌曲中營造的理想德瑞克是假的，但稱讚蜜雪兒的嗓音，不過形容她的演唱風格太像粉絲<ref name="Sources14">{{Cite web |url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/12/k-michelle-anybody-wanna-buy-a-heart-review |title=K. Michelle Trades Brashness for Subtlety on "Anybody Wanna Buy a Heart?" |last=Arceneaux |first=Michael |date=2014-12-11 |website=Complex |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180517082635/http://www.complex.com/music/2014/12/k-michelle-anybody-wanna-buy-a-heart-review |archive-date=2018-05-17 |accessdate=2020-08-24 }}</ref>。《{{tsl|en|The Fader|The Fader}}》的作家稱歌曲「單純很奇怪」和「過於殷勤的音頻版同人小說」<ref name="Source13" />。

